cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper proposes a neural machine translation model that incorporates image information to improve the capturing of the entire meaning of a sentence. This involves the use of latent variables to capture underlying semantics from both text and images. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves training a model end-to-end, which suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The use of latent variables also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing and information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible sub-category.
